I stand before you today as a 24-year-old individual named Chloe Mills, pleading guilty to the offense of affray. It is with great remorse and understanding of the severity of my actions that I address the court.

The unfortunate incident occurred when I discovered that my boyfriend had been unfaithful to me. In a state of deep emotional pain, I made the ill-advised decision to confront him at a bar where I believed he was present. I admit that I resorted to threatening language, insinuating the possession of a firearm, in a desperate attempt to extract information regarding the other person involved.

